Task 2: Create a serial interface for subtracting two numbers using
CPU registers only, store the result in a register, and output all
register values.
You must then examine the SREG status register and clearly
identify the state of the Zero (Z) and Carry (C) flags after the
subtraction.Evidence the SREG behavior and explain why these flags are set
or cleared for this operation, with particular emphasis on how the
AVR represents underflow in unsigned subtraction and how the
Carry flag behaves during subtraction.

By Professor DR ALEXZ FARRALL
